# Cursor agent branch hygiene (`origin/cursor/*`)

## Why this happens

Cursor often creates a **new remote branch per agent run** (e.g. `cursor/missing-test-coverage-xxxx`). If each run finishes without **merging to `main` and deleting the remote branch**, dozens of near-duplicate branches accumulate. They are not harmful to `main`, but they clutter the repo and make ŌĆ£merge everything laterŌĆØ manual work.

## Prevention (default for every agent session)

1. **Prefer one line of integration** ŌĆö When the task is incremental (tests, small fixes), work from **up-to-date `main`** or a **single** integration branch (e.g. `integrate/<topic>-<date>`) and merge to `main` when verified, instead of leaving many parallel `cursor/*` remotes.
2. **End of a successful task** ŌĆö After `npm test` / `npm run build` / `npm run lint` pass (per `end-of-session-workflow.mdc`):
   - **Commit** on the current branch.
   - **Merge or fast-forward to `main`** (or open one PR) and **`git push origin main`** when the user wants production history updated.
   - **Delete the remote agent branch** when work is fully on `main`:  
     `git push origin --delete <branch-name>`  
     (Only if the user does not need that branch for review; ask once if unsure.)
3. **Do not spawn a second `cursor/*` remote** for the same small follow-up (e.g. ŌĆ£fix test typoŌĆØ) ŌĆö continue on the same branch or `main` unless the user asked for isolation.

## After the fact ŌĆö consolidate many `cursor/*` remotes

When many `origin/cursor/*` branches already exist (excluding `codex/*` / `codec/*` if the user asked to ignore them):

1. `git fetch origin --prune`
2. From **`origin/main`**, create an integration branch:  
   `git checkout -b integrate/cursor-backlog-$(date +%F) origin/main`
3. **List unique commits** not yet in `main` across all cursor remotes:  
   `bash scripts/list-cursor-commits-not-in-main.sh`  
   Review the log; remove any SHAs you intentionally skip (e.g. obsolete mega-branches).
4. **Cherry-pick** in listed order (drops empty picks when a patch is already on `main`):  
   `git cherry-pick <sha>...` or loop with `git cherry-pick <sha> --empty=drop`  
   Resolve conflicts once per commit; prefer keeping **`main`-era** behavior when a branch is very old.
5. Verify (`npm test`, `npm run build`, `npm run lint`), **merge to `main`**, **push**, then **delete** merged `origin/cursor/*` branches the user no longer needs.

There is **no fully safe one-click ŌĆ£merge allŌĆØ** for divergent agent branches touching the same files; the script below gives a **reviewable commit list**; cherry-pick integration stays explicit.

## User-side settings (optional)

In **Cursor ŌåÆ Settings**, check **Git / branch** options (wording varies by version): prefer defaulting agents to **current branch** or **`main`** when possible so fewer disposable remotes are created.
